tridb_graph_v1_rewire.patch — advisor plan 025 / ADR-0013 Stage A: rewire both operators'
graph probe from the v0 heap-backed extension (graph_store.neighbors, src/graph_store_ext/)
to the v1 NATIVE adjacency-list access method's external-id traversal
(graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext, src/graph_store/ + the gph_upsert_vertex id-mapping layer).
Applies LAST in the chain, after tridb_operator_arg_hardening.patch.

  * tjs_operator.cpp   graphReachableT:   SELECT dst FROM graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext(%lld)
  * tjs_open_operator.cpp expandMultiSeedO: LATERAL graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext(f.src)

The SPI shape, caching (probe ONCE at Open), single-connection nesting discipline (DEV-1236),
and golden rule 3 (native traversal, never a relational join) are all unchanged — only the
substrate is now the native 32KB-page AM the thesis is about. The SQL-side mapping layer +
v0-compat front door (add_edge/neighbors/visits/graph_query) live in the repo-owned
src/graph_store/graph_store_am--0.1.0.sql, NOT in this vendor patch.

Parity oracle: test/graph_v0v1_parity_test.sql (asserting; byte-identical neighbor sets).
Sentinel (both files): TRIDB: graph v1 rewire
